      <head>Adolf Weisse (1856-1933)</head>
      <div>
        <!-- BODY: -->
        <p><hi rend="bold">Adolf Weisse (1856-1933),</hi>  distinguished character actor, who studied in Vienna, worked in Kassel (1879), Berlin (1885-86), and Cologne (1887-), then at the Deutsches Theater (German People's Theater) in Vienna (1889-), becoming its Director in 1902.  
                
Adolf Weisse was the father of (click on) <ref cRef="weisse_hans">Hans Weisse</ref>.  
                              
<hi rend="italic">Source:</hi> Yates, W E., <hi rend="italic">Theatre in Vienna: A Critical History, 1776-1995</hi> (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 1996), 184</p>
